[4] Norovirus, hotel - UK (Scotland): suspected
Date: Wed 7 Apr 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ic lanarkshire co uk, Wed 7 Apr 2004 [edited]
<http://iclanarkshire.icnetwork.co.uk/news/scotland/headlines/page.cfm?objectid=14127019&method=full&siteid=50144>


Scotland: viral gastroenteritis outbreak hits hotel guests
----------------------------------------------------------
An investigation is under way into an outbreak of gastric flu at one of
Scotland's plushest hotels. The five-star Cameron House Hotel on the banks
of Loch Lomond has played host to a number of top celebrities. But staff
and visitors at the luxury location have been issued a letter warning them
that some guests had been struck down by diarrhea and vomiting.

